Class SFCharStatsRender

java.lang.Object
SFCharStatsRender
public class SFCharStatsRender
extends java.lang.Object

SFCharStatsRender

This class reads data from text files and loads that data into the appropriate type of data structure.

Each method will return data that was loaded in locally for use in AllOutScrap (controller class).

2022-1-10

  • Method Details

    • CharStatsRender

      public java.lang.String[][] CharStatsRender​(java.lang.String strFile, int intRow, int intCol)
      This method reads data from a text file INSIDE the .jar file this class is in and stores it in a 2D array, which will be returned. It always ignores the first line of the text file because it assumes that the first line is table headers for the data.

      Parameters:
      strFile - File INSIDE the .jar file that the user wants to read data from
      intRow - Number of rows to read starting from row 0
      intCol - Number of columns to read starting from column 0
      Returns:
      2D array with data from text file loaded inside it

    • highscores

      public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String[]> highscores()
      This method reads data from a text file called "winners.txt" OUTSIDE the .jar file this class is in, stores it in an ArrayList and returns it.

      Returns:
      ArrayList (maximum size of ArrayList is 15) of String arrays (length of String arrays is 2) where index 0 is the name of the top scorer, and index 1 is the time it took them to win the game.
